Define a new entity "Product" with the following attributes:

1. name -> string, unique, min_length=5
2. description -> string, required
3. quantity -> int, required, default=0
4. price -> float
5. discount -> float

A Product has a category associated and and Category has many Products.

Define all layers including:
* Controller
* Repository
* Service
* DTO (ProductDTO, ProductResponse)
* model

ProductController must implement the following endpoints

* POST /api/admin/categories/{category_id}/products -> Create a new product under a category
* PUT /api/admin/products/{product_id} -> Update a product
* DELETE /api/admin/products/{product_id} -> Delete a product
* GET /api/public/products -> List all products (implement pagination)
* GET /api/public/products/{product_id} -> Get a product by id
* GET /api/public/products/keyword/{keyword} -> List all product by keyword searching over name and description (implement pagination)
* GET /api/public/categories/{category_id}/products -> List all products under a category (implement pagination)

Use existing Category implementation as reference for general guidelines.

Write unitests to cover new controller and service implementations.